Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.780 --> 00:00:04.730
&gt;&gt; From the Library of
Congress in Washington, DC.

00:00:17.350 --> 00:00:20.190
&gt;&gt; Lee Ann Potter: Good morning.

00:00:20.190 --> 00:00:24.410
You know, any time I have the
opportunity to kick off one

00:00:24.410 --> 00:00:27.430
of these events, I
always feel a little bit

00:00:27.430 --> 00:00:30.670
like I should apologize
for interrupting the party.

00:00:30.670 --> 00:00:33.560
So apologies for interrupting
the party, but welcome,

00:00:33.560 --> 00:00:35.260
welcome to the Library
of Congress.

00:00:35.260 --> 00:00:36.560
I'm Lee Ann Potter.

00:00:36.560 --> 00:00:38.220
I direct educational
outreach here.

00:00:38.220 --> 00:00:43.450
And I am thrilled to welcome you
to our symposium on diversity

00:00:43.450 --> 00:00:46.070
in children's literature,
sponsored by the library.

00:00:46.070 --> 00:00:49.500
And, of course, We
Need Diverse Books.

00:00:49.500 --> 00:00:52.510
This morning -- So if you want
to clap or something, feel free.

00:00:52.510 --> 00:00:56.800
[ Applause ]

00:00:56.800 --> 00:00:59.290
As you know, our program
really does have a title.

00:00:59.290 --> 00:01:03.970
We're calling it Seen and
Heard: The Power of Books.

00:01:03.970 --> 00:01:06.310
This program is being
live streamed.

00:01:06.310 --> 00:01:09.530
So I want to give a shout out
to all of those in the audience

00:01:09.530 --> 00:01:11.860
that are at a distance,
especially those

00:01:11.860 --> 00:01:14.750
in time zones other than ours.

00:01:14.750 --> 00:01:17.990
You know, it's 9 o'clock here.

00:01:17.990 --> 00:01:20.580
There's folks in
Chicago are watching.

00:01:20.580 --> 00:01:22.420
There's folks in
Albuquerque are watching.

00:01:22.420 --> 00:01:23.980
Folks in Sacramento
are out there.

00:01:23.980 --> 00:01:27.300
So we appreciate them
getting up for this event.

00:01:27.300 --> 00:01:29.980
And finally, I want
to thank my colleagues

00:01:29.980 --> 00:01:31.850
who are making that happen.

