today with our colleagues

00:54:58.140 --> 00:55:01.530
from We Need Diverse Books,
to highlight diversity

00:55:01.530 --> 00:55:03.020
in children's literature.

00:55:03.020 --> 00:55:06.970
Just four years ago, We
Need Diverse Books began

00:55:06.970 --> 00:55:09.820
as a simple hashtag on Twitter.

00:55:09.820 --> 00:55:14.210
Today, the organization has
grown from a grassroots movement

00:55:14.210 --> 00:55:20.140
into a 5013C nonprofit with
a team that spans the globe.

00:55:20.140 --> 00:55:23.330
Writers and illustrators,
editors and agents,

00:55:23.330 --> 00:55:26.340
book bloggers and book lovers,

00:55:26.340 --> 00:55:29.160
the We Need Diverse Books
team seeks to create a world

00:55:29.160 --> 00:55:31.380
in which every child
can see themselves

00:55:31.380 --> 00:55:33.630
in the pages of a book.

00:55:33.630 --> 00:55:35.920
The Library of Congress
shares this goal.

00:55:35.920 --> 00:55:40.640
We are proud to have hosted this
morning's symposium on diversity

00:55:40.640 --> 00:55:42.720
in children's literature
and also

00:55:42.720 --> 00:55:44.960
to be hosting this ceremony.

00:55:44.960 --> 00:55:46.930
Both events highlight
and promote books

00:55:46.930 --> 00:55:49.460
that broaden our notions
of diversity and engage us

00:55:49.460 --> 00:55:52.730
in meaningful conversations
about them.

00:55:52.730 --> 00:55:55.960
To honor exemplary diverse
books created by writers

00:55:55.960 --> 00:55:58.910
and illustrators from
marginalized communities,

00:55:58.910 --> 00:56:01.780
We Need Diverse Books
established the Walter Dean

00:56:01.780 --> 00:56:04.930
Myers Award for outstanding
children's literature,

00:56:04.930 --> 00:56:07.210
the Walters.

00:56:07.210 --> 00:56:10.710
Walter Dean Myers was
a five-time winner

00:56:10.710 --> 00:56:16.070
of the Coretta Scott King award
and two-time Newbery honors.

00:56:16.070 --> 00:56:18.130
He was named the third
national ambassador

00:56:18.130 --> 00:56:21.480
for Young People's Literature
by the Library of Congress,

00:56:21.480 --> 00:56:22.780
the Children's Book Council

00:56:22.780 --> 00:56:26.770
and the Every Child
a Reader in 2012.

00:56:26.770 --> 00:56:28.480
We are delighted that the MC

00:56:28.480 --> 00:56:32.900
for this morning's ceremony is
the current national ambassador

00:56:32.900 --> 00:56:35.750
for Young People's
Literature, Jacqueline Woodson.

00:56:35.750 --> 00:56:38.510
