01:00:31.320 --> 01:00:32.750
but this is very relevant.

01:00:32.750 --> 01:00:34.760
I do digress.

01:00:34.760 --> 01:00:37.080
That was all to just
kind of cover

01:00:37.080 --> 01:00:41.030
up my flubbing, the
writing here.

01:00:41.030 --> 01:00:42.740
It's a very New Yorker
thing to kind

01:00:42.740 --> 01:00:45.120
of knock you off
track for a minute.

01:00:46.800 --> 01:00:49.400
It is a true universally
acknowledged

01:00:49.400 --> 01:00:51.300
that every diverse
book is in need

01:00:51.300 --> 01:00:54.310
of a bookseller to hand sell it.

01:00:54.310 --> 01:00:57.070
Of all the gatekeepers in
the publishing industry,

01:00:57.070 --> 01:00:59.420
booksellers may be one
of the most important,

01:00:59.420 --> 01:01:01.980
as people who both curate
collections and get books

01:01:01.980 --> 01:01:05.630
into the hands of readers
who will purchase them.

01:01:05.630 --> 01:01:08.960
They have the power to
create book bestsellers,

01:01:08.960 --> 01:01:11.930
