01:23:54.670 --> 01:23:57.510
right.

01:23:57.510 --> 01:24:00.000
Thank you so much
for that, Carol.

01:24:00.000 --> 01:24:02.320
That poem was lovely.

01:24:02.320 --> 01:24:10.880
Oh, man. Eric Velasquez.

01:24:10.880 --> 01:24:16.450
One cool thing is the children's
book writing community is small,

01:24:16.450 --> 01:24:18.160
so we all know each other.

01:24:18.160 --> 01:24:19.460
A lot of us know each other.

01:24:19.460 --> 01:24:21.410
A lot of us go way, way back.

01:24:21.410 --> 01:24:24.570
And when we get together, we
have a lot of catching up to do.

01:24:24.570 --> 01:24:28.190
So it was so great to
be reunited last night

01:24:28.190 --> 01:24:29.660
and to be able to
gossip about all

01:24:29.660 --> 01:24:31.130
that stuff we didn't
get a chance to talk

01:24:31.130 --> 01:24:34.570
about and to catch up.

01:24:34.570 --> 01:24:38.940
And I want to make a point about
the importance of picture books.

01:24:38.940 --> 01:24:41.200
I feel like when
I read Schomburg,

01:24:41.200 --> 01:24:43.850
I learned so much
that I didn't know.

01:24:43.850 --> 01:24:47.230
And I think sometimes we
think picture books are

01:24:47.230 --> 01:24:48.540
for young people.

01:24:48.540 --> 01:24:53.510
They really are for
everyone, so.

01:24:53.510 --> 01:24:57.480
[ Applause ]

01:24:57.480 --> 01:25:00.390
And they're a great way to
teach about the narrative arc.

01:25:00.390 --> 01:25:02.600
They're a great way
to teach poetry.

01:25:02.600 --> 01:25:07.310
So many of the forms
are so poetic.

01:25:07.310 --> 01:25:13.530
So get these books into the
hands of writers of all ages.

01:25:13.530 --> 01:25:17.260
They're groundbreaking and
important and world changing.

01:25:17.260 --> 01:25:20.960
Eric Velasquez is the
illustrator of numerous books

01:25:20.960 --> 01:25:23.560
for children, including
several previous collections

01:25:23.560 --> 01:25:26.840
with Carole Boston Weatherford.

01:25:26.840 --> 01:25:30.010
He won the John Steptoe New
